main event: Multiple witnesses, including pilots, observed a bright, glowing, round object with pieces breaking off over Spokane, Washington on September 20, 1960.
interesting points: The object was observed by several witnesses at different altitudes and locations, indicating it was a real phenomenon.
The object displayed unusual characteristics, such as pieces breaking off while continuing to glow.
The object moved rapidly and disappeared rapidly, making it difficult to identify.
Radar contact was made with the object, in addition to the visual sightings.
The Air Force was unable to conclusively identify the object and listed it as unexplained.
sighted object: a bright, glowing, round object with pieces breaking off
